manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: About Us DeepCool was founded with the mission of providing performance PC hardware and thermal solutions for enthusiasts across the world. Through dedicated independent R&D and manufacturing, DeepCool continues to expand its portfolio of products that empower gamers and enthusiasts to build better systems that meet the rapid paces of technology. The Beast mode for your AK620---FK120 High-Performance PWM Fan Carefully constructed and tested to enhance static pressure and concentrate airflow for outstanding cooling performance on any mounting application including cooler heat sinks, radiators, and case fan configurations. The narrow frame bezel and wide fan blade provides increased surface area to deliver higher efficiency.

ELITE COOLING Extremely efficient with a PWM range up to 1850RPM that maximizes air pressure and airflow for impressive cooling results while offering dynamic balance between high performance and low-noise operation. 500-1850 RPM Dynamic PWM Range 2.19 mmAq Max Static Pressure 68.99 CFM Max Airflow

OUTSTANDING DETAILS High-quality polybutylene terephthalate (PBT) material is used to ensure increased durability and wear resistance, allowing the fan blades to maintain high tensile strength. Shock-absorbing rubber pads shield the screw mounts to reduce unnecessary vibrations for stable operation.

SUPER SILENT Maxing out at just 28dbA under full load, the extremely silent FK120 fan is exceptionally designed for quiet noise levels. The fluid dynamic bearing provides superior performance and reliable long-term stability.

Fan Dimensions 120×120×25 mm Net Weight 527 g Fan Speed 500~1850 RPM±10% Fan Airflow 68.99 CFM Fan Air Pressure 2.19 mmAq Fan Noise ≤28 dB(A) Fan Connector 4-pin PWM Bearing Type Fluid Dynamic Bearing Fan Rated Voltage 12 VDC Fan Rated Current 0.12 A Fan Power Consumption 1.44 W

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 21, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars They move some air.
reviews.reviewText: I was looking around for parts to do an all black, no lighting build. If you're looking for a no frills, good performing fan, these are the ones. I put 5 in my nzxt h5 flow (3 intake, 2 exhaust). I also added them to the deepcool Ak400 Zero dark plus in a push/pull config, and they keep my 5800x3d just as cool as a 240mm AIO would. First pic is with a 5600x, but i swapped it out for a 5800x3d about a week after. My whole setup together with these fans, and this case, and 3080 at full load, in a game, doesn't go over 70c, and the 5800x3d, sits right around 65c, at 1440p. I've had pretty much every fan, from corsair, to noctua, and nzxt. For the price to performance, these beat them all, and remain nearly silent while doing so.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 10, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I recently built a new PC and purchased a case that included 3 fans on the front and one on the rear. After I had built the PC, I discovered that the fans in the case were actually relatively weak, with the front fans only rated for about 1200 RPM. Since I was going to replace the front fans with some rather powerful 2100 RPM fans, I figured I should put some fans that were almost as powerful along the top for venting to reach a near-neutral pressure inside the case when keeping the rear fan the same. I went with these fans from DeepCool due to their RPM and CFM ratings, and I don't regret it. I can hear the fans when they reach their max RPM, but it's only the sound of air moving, nowhere near the noise level of other fans that sound like jet engines. They do a great job of venting air from my case and, when combined with my cpu cooler and front fans, they keep my i7-13700K cpu in the range of 50-60 degrees Celsius under heavy load. The fans come with a magnetic fan hub to attach inside the case that allows you to power up to 4 fans off of only 1 chassis fan header on the motherboard, making installation and cable management somewhat easier. Something worth mentioning is that these fans are the exact same as the stock fans for the DeepCool AK620 Digital cpu cooler. Like I said, these are great fans, but beware Amazon drivers who don't care. I had to send my first set of fans back because the product packaging was not protected by anything like bubble wrap or foam, and the fans arrived damaged from being thrown around. For the second set that they sent me, they apparently learned their lesson and at least put the product in a bubble mailer. This, of course, has nothing to do with the manufacturer and everything to do with Amazon not thinking when packaging a product.

reviews.reviewTitle: Excelente, solo un detalle que me molesto.
reviews.reviewText: 1 Empaque presionado y eso que llego sobre otra caja. Pero eso es lo de menos, es solo una caja de papel.2 El peso de los Ventiladores se nota buena calidad, excelente porque trae gomas de fabrica.3 Los accesorios bien, es lo que indica el producto.4 diseño minimalista, fácil de limpiar.Lo bueno.Lo use con un Hyper 212 (Coolermaster), coloque dos(1 en cada lado).El procesador es un R7 5800X, esta limitado a 99% de uso en el procesador.Gabinete NZXT H510. No panel frontal perforado ni cristal.La temperatura fue medida con la app NZXT y HWMonitor.Temperatura normal 45-47, carga normal 54-57 y con cargar 66 no sube ni siquiera a 70.La carga es con edición 4k y juegos AAA en ultra 4k.Anteriormente tenia 3 Ventiladores en el Enfriador y llegaba a la misma temperatura, ahora con solo 2 hace la misma función.Coloque el 3er Ventilador a la PSU (fuente de poder) y las temperaturas mejoraron extraordinariamente, antes se apagaba por calentamiento y el PSU estaba muy caliente pero ahora esta fresco.Y lo MALO, es que solamente uno llego con falso en cable, necesito hacer presión para que embone con el conector a PC. Siempre qué limpio tengo problemas con el cable qué hace falso, "No es mi MOBO ni el accesorio que incluye".Me molesta porque Por la caja que viene abierta y maltratada, creo que sería porque revisan los Ventiladores antes de enviarlos pero es al contrario.
El producto cumple al 100% con las expectativas. Al ser envíado en bolsa, la caja sufrió daños serios en el proceso.
